beer.beer_description:
Clean. Crisp. Ready for adventure.

Based on the German Kolsch style, this beer uses simply one type of malted barley and one hop variety to make this your easy drinking companion.

The Foundation for National Parks and Wildlife (FNPW) is the charity partner of Australia’s National Parks. National Parks are the landscapes of some of our best memories. They are also home to uniquely Australian species found nowhere else on earth.

FNPW proudly protect these awesome treasures for those that will come after us, and are the charity partner of For the Road Draught.

items.badge_description: Your quest to quench your thirst leaves no stone unturned! That's at least That's 265 distinct venues!

Wine isn't the only beverage worthy of pairing with a delicious meal. With so many styles widely available, there’s a perfect pint for any cuisine of your choosing. That's a beer at 60 different venues categorized as a Restaurant. Try 5 more for Level 13!
One cannot live on dank hops alone. Tone down the bitterness and enjoy some smooth flavor. That's 65 different beers with an IBU of 20 or below. Try 5 more for Level 14!

There's beer in them thar hills! You're setting off on your journey through the world of beer, but be sure to take a little time to get to know each brewery as you go. That's a beer from 210 different breweries. Try 5 more for Level 43!
